Data
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ BalanceOf
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when account and id are queried
в”‚   в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should return the balance for that (account, id)
в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ when account is zero address
в”‚       в””в”Ђв”Ђ it may return 0 (no revert)
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ BalanceOfBatch
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when accounts.length != ids.length
в”‚   в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should revert with ERC1155InvalidArrayLength
в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ when accounts.length == ids.length
в”‚       в”њв”Ђв”Ђ it should return an array of balances in order
в”‚       в””в”Ђв”Ђ when arrays are empty
в”‚           в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should return an empty array
в””в”Ђв”Ђ IsApprovedForAll
    в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when operator has not been approved
    в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should return false
    в””в”Ђв”Ђ when operator has been approved
        в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should return true

Approve
в””в”Ђв”Ђ SetApprovalForAll
    в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when operator is the zero address
    в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should revert (if enforced) or document behavior
    в””в”Ђв”Ђ when operator is not the zero address
        в”њв”Ђв”Ђ it should set isApprovedForAll[account][operator] to approved
        в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should emit ApprovalForAll

Transfer
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ SafeTransferFrom
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when from or to is zero address
в”‚   в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should revert
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when caller is not owner and not approved for all
в”‚   в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should revert with ERC1155MissingApprovalForAll
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when balance of from for id is less than value
в”‚   в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should revert with ERC1155InsufficientBalance
в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ when preconditions hold
в”‚       в”њв”Ђв”Ђ it should decrement balance of from for id by value
в”‚       в”њв”Ђв”Ђ it should increment balance of to for id by value
в”‚       в”њв”Ђв”Ђ it should emit TransferSingle
в”‚       в””в”Ђв”Ђ when to is a contract
в”‚           в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should call onERC1155Received and respect return value or revert
в””в”Ђв”Ђ SafeBatchTransferFrom
    в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when ids.length != values.length
    в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should revert with ERC1155InvalidArrayLength
    в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when from or to is zero address
    в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should revert
    в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when caller is not owner and not approved for all
    в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should revert with ERC1155MissingApprovalForAll
    в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when any balance is insufficient
    в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should revert with ERC1155InsufficientBalance
    в””в”Ђв”Ђ when preconditions hold
        в”њв”Ђв”Ђ it should update all balances and emit TransferBatch
        в””в”Ђв”Ђ when to is a contract
            в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should call onERC1155BatchReceived and respect return value or revert

Mint
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ Mint
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when to is zero address
в”‚   в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should revert with ERC1155InvalidReceiver
в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ when to is not zero address
в”‚       в”њв”Ђв”Ђ it should increment balance of to for id by value
в”‚       в”њв”Ђв”Ђ it should emit TransferSingle from address(0) to to
в”‚       в””в”Ђв”Ђ when to is a contract
в”‚           в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should call onERC1155Received and respect return value or revert
в””в”Ђв”Ђ MintBatch
    в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when to is zero address
    в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should revert with ERC1155InvalidReceiver
    в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when ids.length != values.length
    в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should revert with ERC1155InvalidArrayLength
    в””в”Ђв”Ђ when preconditions hold
        в”њв”Ђв”Ђ it should increment balances and emit TransferBatch
        в””в”Ђв”Ђ when to is a contract
            в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should call onERC1155BatchReceived and respect return value or revert

Burn
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ Burn
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when from is zero address
в”‚   в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should revert
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when balance of from for id is less than value
в”‚   в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should revert with ERC1155InsufficientBalance
в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ when balance is sufficient
в”‚       в”њв”Ђв”Ђ it should decrement balance of from for id by value
в”‚       в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should emit TransferSingle to address(0)
в””в”Ђв”Ђ BurnBatch
    в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when from is zero address
    в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should revert
    в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when ids.length != values.length
    в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should revert with ERC1155InvalidArrayLength
    в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when any balance is insufficient
    в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should revert with ERC1155InsufficientBalance
    в””в”Ђв”Ђ when preconditions hold
        в”њв”Ђв”Ђ it should decrement all balances
        в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should emit TransferBatch to address(0)

Metadata
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ Uri
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when no token-specific URI is set
в”‚   в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should return the default uri
в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ when a token-specific URI is set (via Mod)
в”‚       в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should return baseURI + tokenURIs[id] or documented behavior
в””в”Ђв”Ђ SetBaseURI_SetTokenURI
    в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should update storage so uri(id) returns the expected value

ExportSelectors
в””в”Ђв”Ђ for each ERC1155 facet (core, metadata, etc.)
    в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should return an abi.encodePacked list of that facet's external function selectors in the expected order
